This paper deals with the issue of advertising disclosure on social media platforms, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social media (cs.SI). The study involves analyzing large amounts of data from YouTube and Pinterest, which involves data mining and machine learning techniques (cs.MM). The paper also discusses policy suggestions to improve advertising disclosure practices, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
